attributes.content: ...It's autumn.
The hawthorns have sweetened around this time. The children most loved eating hawthorn fruits.
...It's another day.
How much life do I still have left?
When I shut my eyes, I remember so many things of the past...
...and all night, I'm sleepless.
...Dusk?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Why are you here...?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: You don't seem shocked at all.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Living to this age, the things that shock you, dwindle fast... *cough*, *cough*. But talking to you about this... it all pales in comparison.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: We haven't seen each other... for how many years?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I can't remember. Likely decades.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: ...You really are Dusk.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: You still remember me.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: How do you know you're not in one of my paintings, with the life you've lived?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: I couldn't be.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Are you that sure?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Dusk, you saved me, and I lived in your paintings for such a long time... I can tell it apart.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: *cough*, *cough*...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: This is the bet we made. Whether there'd come a day I'd see through your paintings at a glance, through your worlds, and through you.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: But ever since we parted that day, you never saw me again... I'd thought I'd never have another chance... to talk with you again.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: ...Those who can talk with me like this... are few in the first place.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: ...For such a long time, I've thought back again and again on those days. That pavilion... far from Catastrophes, famine, refuge. A normal pavilion.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: It was just like a dream... *cough*, *cough*.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I believed you'd be quite a good painter. All your life, you never actually took up the brush. Wasn't that such a waste of my teaching?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Painter. A painter, a great painter. After meeting you, who could still call themselves a painter?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: There've been a seldom few. All of them were... strange people.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: ...Then I really have disappointed you.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Who knows.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Just maybe... you surprised me more than anyone else.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Meeting again after so many years... it's like we don't have much to say. I'm so old and worn. I've finished this life of mine. And you... you're still the same you as ever.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Do you have anything you'd like to talk about?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: No... I'm... very content.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: You saved me. You gave me the chance to keep living... and even here on my deathbed, you've come.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I'm so gratified, Dusk, to see you... still looking like this.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Your eyes...
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: I'm very old, Dusk. Illness has tormented me for so many years...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I somehow want to ask you now... watching the people you know die one by one, do you ever feel lonely?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: What kind of nonsense is that?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Then what goes through your mind?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Sometimes, I'll feel sorry. Sometimes, I'll feel rueful too.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Look at you... finally willing to speak the truth.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Do you still remember what I told you, about my hometown utterly ruined by Catastrophe?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: It's already far, too far away to try and remember now... it's the reflection in my memories. It isn't behind me anymore. They're a distant place in front of me...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I... I never took up my own brush.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Because if I ever tried in my life to paint, I would only paint... *cough*, *cough*, my hometown.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: You clearly can't remember anything of it.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: That's right. Even if I cast my mind back... apart from the single name of 'P'o-shan Village,' I wouldn't remember a single thing.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: It doesn't have much in the way of good memories, but I always end up dreaming of it. Dreaming of so many... homelands. Tell me. In all this lifetime, where is it I've wanted to return?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Dusk.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Hmm?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Could you help me... paint that P'o-shan Village?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: I only remember... next to my house, was a pawn shop. Its bookkeeper... wore such beautiful clothes, so gentle and elegant. When I was young, I thought... I'd like to be a bookkeeper too.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: The village didn't have any of those strange moving plates. It was farm fields and gathering places growing unrestrained, and wherever they were made, people would be. Just like oilseed flowers...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: If you wandered a little too far, you'd see a distant mountain...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: That mountain... I always got lost there in my dreams. There were terrible monsters there... Catastrophe clouds, floating around its peak... that's the landscape I can remember most clearly.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Without me saying much more, you have a sense of it too, don't you?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Of course. Not a single part missing.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: How I wish the years could've stayed where I was young. Us, living on the mountains. Me, learning to paint from you, helping you sometimes to grind the ink...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Dusk.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Mm.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: You've met so many oddities. Seen so many changes in the land...
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Tell me your view, for me. Would you say... *cough*, *cough*.
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Would you say I lived... a blessed life?
attributes.name: Dawn

attributes.content: Yo. You're up?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: I've come to understand... why you wanted to bring me here.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: ...There's all of these people.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Wanna go for mahjong? We're missing a fourth.
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: You... you get out of here. I'm not going.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Hey, you were all pumped to watch movies last night and now you've gone cold kiddo mode again?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: It's no big deal to like movies. I've got a jumbo collection here.
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: What even are all those? Churned-out cut-and-paste covers, completely meaningless long names, and just watching makes you fed up. Get rid of them!
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: How could you say that!?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: I've seen no shortage of operation archives. What kind of person is this Doctor?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Oh? You sneaked them out? Didn't set Closure off?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: You mean that young devil? She didn't mind me. I went there directly.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Wha... why would... is she just aiming at me?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: What relationship does the Censor have with Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: That's another thing entirely. It's no problem, so don't get worked up. Leizi's a down-and-out exile, and she doesn't ever even come to Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: You mind her that much? Were officials out there hassling you?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: Hmph. I don't pay mind to that little Censor, but I care about where her Lei Fa originates from... her master, and those elders always watching over us, are no end of trouble.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: You say I was bound in my own circle? He burnt scrolls outright, set thorough fire to the mountains and rivers before my eyes, bent on teaching me a lesson. I'm not like you. You get someone constantly berating you and it never dawns on you that you're bugging them.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: I annoyed him. Annoyed him to the point I could die. There's nothing I can do with him.
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Ho ho, some pretty wild stuff went down, huh?
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: You still haven't told me. What kind of person is this Doctor, and that Kal’tsit? What does you staying here have to do with the two of them?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Also, where are they currently?
attributes.name: Dusk

attributes.content: Alrighty. I'll tell you everything.
attributes.name: Nian

attributes.content: And this way you'll learn... why I like this place so much.
attributes.name: Nian
